content.description: Fun, short climb with good holds.
content.protection: Medium to Large pro needed to set up TR anchors.
content.location: 10 feet to left of Amazon from Ozegna crack.

content.description: First, stand behind this fin so you cannot see the valley. Climb straight up the center on some slopers and pinchers with very tricky feet on the right of a small bulge. Staying to the left this could be a 5.10 Var.
content.protection: Med to large gear for T.R.

content.description: The route is named after Brian Long himself. The route follows a crack system up about 10 feet, then traverses right and up through easier climbing.
content.protection: Standard rack. No fixed anchors at the top
content.location: Dirty little pig boy is the first route on the right side of the fin when coming down the approach trail.

content.description: Follow the obvious right leaning crack to the left of Girls Just Wanna Have Fin. Crawl through the arch and finish up the steep yet positive face to the right.
content.location: South side of the Fin on the East face (where the valley is out of sight).

content.description: First, stand behind this fin so you cannot see the valley. Now, faceing the arch in this formation, climb the crack on the left-center
content.protection: Small nuts, and cams of all sizes.

content.description: Start at the corner of the fin closest to the trail along the bottom of the cliff. Pull through two roof tiers to very easy climbing up top.
content.protection: Cams in horizontals, tricams may be useful

climbs.name: Amazon From Ozegna aka Short Italian Girls

content.description: Some call this route a tough 5.8, while others call it an easy 5.7. Either way, the tough part is at the start then follows up and over some bulgy overhangs.
content.protection: Med to Large pro for TR.
content.location: 10 ft right of Part Man, Part Monkey.

content.description: Work past a tough start then straight up over the overhangs.
content.protection: Good TR anchors and typical Annapolis rack for lead.
content.location: Start 7 feet right of Amazon from Ozegna crack

content.description: Start at the corner of the fin closest to the road and head up and right through three roofs towards a dead tree growing along side the climb. Pretty much an "all roof climb".
content.protection:
Cams/tricams, nuts are a tough sell in the horizontals. 

  Med to large gear for TR.

content.description: A small, single fin of rock 200 feet south of Faint's Roof.
